summary: This collection of documents pertains to the relationship between the FBI and the CIA, covering topics such as information sharing protocols, requests for tours of FBI facilities by CIA personnel, and handling of alien interview requests. It also includes information regarding potential CIA contributions to the National Council of Churches and concerns over the coordination of joint operations.
title: CIA, NATIONAL STUDENT ASSOC, PICKETING, DEMONSTRATION; RELATIONS WITH CIA; COMMUNIST PARTY OF VENEZUELA; CENTRAL INTELLIGENCE AGENCY (CIA) Operations in the United States
recipient: Secretary of State, Mr. Rosen, Mr. W. C. Sullivan
sender: Director, FBI; FELEGAT, HONG KONG; R. I. Shroder; D. J. Brennan, Jr.; SAC, WTO; MR. I. W. CONRAD; W. O. Cregar
